<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1510">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/162.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-02">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Reported that Carranza issued orders to Villa today that further
                                investigations of Benton case should cease for present and that
                                Villa refrain from any further discussion of case with either
                                American or British representatives.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>